    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="751"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-07">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">December</hi> 7, 1895</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1203.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information a copy of a
                    resolution of the United States Senate calling for all the correspondence
                    relating to the arrest, trial, conviction, and sentence of Julio Sanguily, and
                    directing that a copy of the record of the trial be obtained.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to obtain and forward to this Department as soon as
                    practicable a certified copy of the record.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#center">[Senate resolution, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1895-12-05">December 5, 1895</date>.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">imprisonment of general sanguily</hi>.</p>
                    <p>Mr. Call submitted the following resolution; which was considered by
                        unanimous consent, and agreed to:</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That the Secretary of State be directed to
                        send to the Senate all correspondence relating to the trial, conviction, and
                        sentence to hard labor for life of <pb facs="0912" n="818" xml:id="pg_818"/>
                        General Sanguily, an American citizen, for alleged complicity in the war
                        against Spain by the Cubans, and if no authentic record should be on tile in
                        the State Department, that the Secretary of State be directed to obtain a
                        copy of the record of such trial.</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
